Pretoria — The Angolan delegation to the Japan-Africa Economic Forum informed on Friday Japanese authorities and businessmen about measures being implemented in the country to create a welcoming business environment for the private sector and foreign investment. This was said on Friday in Johannesburg by the Minister of Economy, Pedro Luís da Fonseca, together with Industry Minister Bernarda Martins, who represented Angola at the Japan-Africa Public-Private Economic Forum, held on 3 and 4 May. The official said so during a meeting with the Minister of Economy, Trade and Industry of Japan, Hiroshige Sek. According to Pedro Luís da Fonseca, the Angolan delegation also held separate meetings with representatives of some multinational brands, especially Toyota and Toshiba, who were also informed about what is being done in Angola in favor of private investment, aiming for the country's economic growth.